{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17639071","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17639071"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T19:03:08+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T19:03:08+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17760"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17760","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17760"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0,0.05,0.14,0.24,0.57]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10474"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75825"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10474","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10474"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17760"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61338"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"1"},{"type":"tags","id":"24"},{"type":"tags","id":"34"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"735"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4943"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"5160"},{"type":"tags","id":"9222"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"24446"},{"type":"contributions","id":"24448"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75825","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/75825"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 28-year-old man presents to the Emergency Department with a right shoulder dislocation sustained while playing rugby. He has no significant medical history and does not take any regular medications. On examination, he appears in pain but is otherwise well. His pulse rate is 88/min, blood pressure 130/80 mmHg, respiratory rate 16/min, SpO2 99% on room air, and temperature 36.7\u00b0C. The right shoulder is visibly deformed and held in an abducted position. The patient is given intravenous Midazolam prior to the reduction of the dislocation.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the primary function of Midazolam in this scenario?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Prevent infection","Reduce inflammation","Induce general anaesthesia","Provide analgesia","Facilitate muscle relaxation"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFacilitate muscle relaxation\u003C/strong\u003E is the primary function of Midazolam in this scenario. Midazolam is a benzodiazepine that acts on the central nervous system to provide sedation, anxiolysis, and muscle relaxation, which are beneficial during the reduction of a dislocated joint. Muscle relaxation decreases muscle spasms around the dislocated joint.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EProvide analgesia\u003C/strong\u003E is not the primary function of Midazolam. It has some mild analgesic effects due to its sedative properties, but is not primarily used for pain relief.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EInduce general anaesthesia\u003C/strong\u003E is not the role of midazolam in this context. Midazolam is used for conscious sedation rather than full anaesthesia, allowing the patient to remain responsive but relaxed during the procedure.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPrevent infection\u003C/strong\u003E is not a function of Midazolam. Infection prevention would involve aseptic techniques and possibly antibiotics.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EReduce inflammation\u003C/strong\u003E is not an effect of Midazolam. Anti-inflammatory medications, such as non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drugs (NSAIDs), would be used for this purpose if needed.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Midazolam is a benzodiazepine used for its sedative and anxiolytic properties during procedures.","It provides muscle relaxation, which can facilitate the reduction of a dislocated joint.","Midazolam also has amnesic effects."],"references":["Baden DN, Visser MFL, Roetman MH, Smeeing DPJ, Houwert RM, Groenwold RHH, van der Meijden OAJ. Effects of reduction technique for acute anterior shoulder dislocation without sedation or intra-articular pain management: a systematic review and meta-analysis. Eur J Trauma Emerg Surg. 2023 Jun;49(3):1383-1392. doi: 10.1007/s00068-023-02242-8. Epub 2023 Mar 1. PMID: 36856781; PMCID: PMC10229450.","Lachance PA. Reduction of shoulder dislocation: are communication and adequate relaxation more important than technique? Can Fam Physician. 2012 Nov;58(11):1189-90, e613-4. PMID: 23152452; PMCID: PMC3498008.","Bambaren IA, Dominguez F, Elias Martin ME, Dom\u00ednguez S. Anesthesia and Analgesia in the Patient with an Unstable Shoulder. Open Orthop J. 2017 Aug 31;11:848-860. doi: 10.2174/1874325001711010848. PMID: 29114334; PMCID: PMC5646176.","Afzalimoghaddam M, Khademi MF, Mirfazaelian H, Payandemehr P, Karimialavijeh E, Jalali A. Comparing Diazepam Plus Fentanyl With Midazolam Plus Fentanyl in the Moderate Procedural Sedation of Anterior Shoulder Dislocations: A Randomized Clinical Trial. J Emerg Med. 2021 Jan;60(1):1-7. doi: 10.1016/j.jemermed.2020.09.030. Epub 2020 Oct 21. PMID: 33097351."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61338"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17760"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61338","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/61338"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-31T20:52:56+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-31T20:52:56+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10474"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75825"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},